SIMPLE: trailer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trailer
<hw>Trail"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, trails.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trailer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trailer
<hw>Trail"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a wheeled vehicle
without a motor, designed to be drawn by a motor vehicle in front of
it;</def> <specif>specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>such a
vehicle used on street railroads. Called also <altname>trail
car</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>the large wheeled wagon or van
pulled by a tractor in a tractor-trailer combination.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>a vehicle equipped as a mobile dwelling unit, pulled by an
automobile or other mtor vehicle, and used as a dwelling when parked; --
also called a <altname>mobile home</altname>.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>A
wheeled motorless open wagon designed to carry a heavy object, such as a
boat <ex>trailer</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Movies)</fld> <def>A short blank segment of movie
film attached to the end; -- used for convenient insertion of the film
in a projector.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Movies)</fld> <def>A short film consisting
primarily of one or more short portions of a film, used in promotions or
advertisements shortly before initial release of a film.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A part of an object which extends some distance
beyond the main body of the object; <as>as, the <ex>trailer</ex> of a
plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>trailer park</b></col>. <cd>An area equipped to
accommodate trailers{2}, often with outlets supplying electrical power
and water. Called also <altname>trailer camp</altname>, <altname>trailer
court</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trailing</ent>⟦br⟧
